edu.wpi.first.wpijavacv
Class WPIDisposable

java.lang.Object
  edu.wpi.first.wpijavacv.WPIDisposable
Direct Known Subclasses:
WPICamera, WPIImage, WPILaptopCamera
public abstract class WPIDisposable
extends java.lang.Object

This class is an abstract class defining disposable elements. It is the superclass of most things which links directly to the javacv core.

Method Detail

dispose

public void dispose()
Disposes this object. This may be called multiple times. Programmers should call this when they no longer need an object. However, even if they don't, this will be called when this object is collected by the garbage collector.

disposed

protected abstract void disposed()
This is called when dispose() is called for the first time. Subclasses should clear out whatever internal resources they are using.
